      <div class="about container w3-padding-large" id="about">
        <div class="text-one">
          <h2>About Us</h2>
          <p>Blood donors are individuals who selflessly give blood to aid others, regardless of compensation. They represent diverse demographics, spanning ages, ethnicities, and socio-economic backgrounds. Prior to donation, donors undergo health screenings to ensure safety and eligibility. Their blood types and compatibility are crucial for successful transfusions, addressing various medical needs. Through their impactful contributions, donors bolster community health systems, embodying compassion and solidarity in saving lives.</p>
          
        </div>
        <div class="text-one">
          <h2>Our Vision</h2>
          <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

</head>
<body>
    <h6>Common Variations of Blood Donation</h6>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Whole Blood Donation:</strong> The most common type where donors give a pint of whole blood.</li>
        <li><strong>Apheresis Donation:</strong> Automated method allowing selective collection of specific blood components.</li>
        <li><strong>Directed Donation:</strong> Donors give blood specifically for a known recipient, often a family member or friend.</li>
        <li><strong>Autologous Donation:</strong> Individuals donate blood for their own future use, ensuring compatibility for planned surgeries.</li>
        <li><strong>Cord Blood Donation:</strong> Collection of stem cell-rich blood from the umbilical cord after childbirth, used in treating various diseases.</li>
    </ul>
</body>
